<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870701-0036 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:International Business Machines Corp.</HL><DD> 07/01/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> IBMCOMPUTERS (EDP) </IN><TEXT>   INTERNATIONAL BUSINESS MACHINES CORP., Armonk, N.Y., introduced a version of its new PS personal computer designed for secretaries. The product, the Personal Typing System, lets a user switch back and forth from word processing on a screen to typing directly on paper. IBM said the computer is currently available and has a suggested price of $2,895. </TEXT></DOC>